{"id": "EUVD-2025-5250", "enisaUuid": "f238db66-ca11-3f26-8031-6231c430e609", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nwifi: ath12k: fix read pointer after free in ath12k_mac_assign_vif_to_vdev()\n\nIn ath12k_mac_assign_vif_to_vdev(), if arvif is created on a different\nradio, it gets deleted from that radio through a call to\nath12k_mac_unassign_link_vif(). This action frees the arvif pointer.\nSubsequently, there is a check involving arvif, which will result in a\nread-after-free scenario.\n\nFix this by moving this check after arvif is again assigned via call to\nath12k_mac_assign_link_vif().\n\nTested-on: QCN9274 hw2.0 PCI WLAN.WBE.1.3.1-00173-QCAHKSWPL_SILICONZ-1", "datePublished": "2025-02-27T03:34:01", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-02T15:30:12", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-57995", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5a10971c7645a95f5d5dc23c26fbac4bf61801d0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f3a95a312419e4f1e992525917da9dbcd247038f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/57100b87c77818cb0d582a92e5cb32fff85c757d"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-57995", "GHSA-7x7f-m8j9-p3cw"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "117b7ce3-4f27-3da6-8c5b-d0795f565d24", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b5068bc9180d06a5ac242b0f9263047c14f86211 <57100b87c77818cb0d582a92e5cb32fff85c757d"}, {"id": "18522970-2c23-302d-893a-bfe6c4caaf48", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14"}, {"id": "39472b9d-fb15-3e12-ba58-531bbe150829", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.57"}, {"id": "5926dff3-84b3-3ba8-a44c-f8ec71371afa", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b5068bc9180d06a5ac242b0f9263047c14f86211 <5a10971c7645a95f5d5dc23c26fbac4bf61801d0"}, {"id": "7208eea3-a6f1-3b34-ab3e-95541c7f9fd9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_ver